text: The Alpine chough (Pyrrhocorax graculus) is a type of bird in the crow family. It is one of only two species in the genus Pyrrhocorax. It nests in the mountains. It can be found in Spain and Morocco eastwards through southern Europe to the Himalayas. The golden eagle is a predator on the chough. ==References== Category:Corvids Category:Birds of Europe Category:Birds of Asia Category:Birds of Africa
